             Apr 25, 2018
            </span>
            <h4>
             <a href="https://healthcare.utah.edu/publicaffairs/news/2018/04/cannabinoids-research.php" target="_blank">
              Grant Paves Way for U of U Researchers to Use Brain-Imaging Technology to Study Effects of Cannabinoids
             </a>
            </h4>
            <span class="tags">
             <a href="//uofuhealth.utah.edu/newsroom/index.php?tag=radiology">
              radiology
             </a>
            </span>
            <p>
             University of Utah Health is proud to announce that it has recently received a $740,000 grant to study personalized effects of cannabinoids through the use of advanced brain imaging.  The medical use of cannabinoids across an increasing number of conditions is now permitted in 29 states and counting, yet critical questions remain unanswered. ...
             <a href="https://healthcare.utah.edu/publicaffairs/news/2018/04/cannabinoids-research.php" target="_blank">
