            <h4>
             <a href="https://unews.utah.edu/treatment-reverses-signs-of-two-degenerative-brain-diseases-als-and-ataxia-in-mice/" target="_blank">
              Treatment Reverses Signs of Two Degenerative Brain Diseases, ALS and Ataxia, In Mice
             </a>
            </h4>
            <span class="tags">
             <a href="//uofuhealth.utah.edu/newsroom/index.php?tag=neurology">
              neurology
             </a>
            </span>
            <p>
             Scientists report a significant step toward combatting two degenerative brain diseases that chip away at an individual’s ability to move, and think. A targeted therapy developed by scientists at University of Utah Health slows the progression of a condition in mice that mimics a rare disease called ataxia....
             <a href="https://unews.utah.edu/treatment-reverses-signs-of-two-degenerative-brain-diseases-als-and-ataxia-in-mice/" target="_blank">
